{
  "video_id": "pcF6IRpe-Og",
  "title": "How I went from child refugee to international model | Halima Aden",
  "es": 0,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 13592.0,
      "end_time": 15809.0,
      "text": "This is me at age seven."
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 17839.0,
      "end_time": 19537.0,
      "text": "And this is also me."
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 21160.0,
      "end_time": 24821.0,
      "text": "(Applause and cheering)"
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 24845.0,
      "end_time": 29191.0,
      "text": "To be standing here in Kakuma refugee camp feels so surreal,"
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 29215.0,
      "end_time": 31676.0,
      "text": "and I&#39;m overcome with so much emotion."
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 32255.000000000004,
      "end_time": 34258.0,
      "text": "These very grounds are where I was born"
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 34282.0,
      "end_time": 36458.0,
      "text": "and spent the first seven years of my life."
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 37878.0,
      "end_time": 39958.0,
      "text": "I think many people are surprised to hear"
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 39982.0,
      "end_time": 42510.0,
      "text": "that I had a great upbringing here at Kakuma."
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 43250.0,
      "end_time": 44499.0,
      "text": "But I was happy,"
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 44523.0,
      "end_time": 46989.0,
      "text": "I was smart, I had friends"
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 47130.0,
      "end_time": 49908.0,
      "text": "and above all, I had hope for a brighter future."
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 50842.0,
      "end_time": 53921.0,
      "text": "That&#39;s not to say that we didn&#39;t have our obstacles."
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 53945.0,
      "end_time": 55576.0,
      "text": "I mean, boy were there struggles."
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 55600.0,
      "end_time": 58900.0,
      "text": "I would sometimes get sick with malaria"
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 58114.0,
      "end_time": 61571.0,
      "text": "and didn&#39;t always know where our next meal would come from."
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 61596.0,
      "end_time": 65210.0,
      "text": "But the sense of community that is here in Kakuma"
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 65459.99999999999,
      "end_time": 67491.0,
      "text": "and the pride that everyone here possesses"
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 67515.0,
      "end_time": 69474.0,
      "text": "is simply unparalleled."
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 71716.0,
      "end_time": 74771.0,
      "text": "When I was younger, I remember conflicts breaking out."
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 75155.0,
      "end_time": 78414.0,
      "text": "That tends to happen when people come from different backgrounds"
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 78438.0,
      "end_time": 80302.0,
      "text": "and don&#39;t speak the same language."
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 80326.0,
      "end_time": 81607.0,
      "text": "Eventually, Swahili --"
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 81631.0,
      "end_time": 82870.0,
      "text": "the main language here --"
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 82894.0,
      "end_time": 84960.0,
      "text": "became our common ground."
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 84867.0,
      "end_time": 86795.0,
      "text": "I made friends with the kids at the camp"
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 86819.0,
      "end_time": 89502.0,
      "text": "and even started embracing some of their cultures,"
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 89526.0,
      "end_time": 93172.0,
      "text": "celebrating holidays like Christmas even though I was raised Muslim."
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 93772.0,
      "end_time": 96462.0,
      "text": "The other kids would embrace my culture as well,"
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 96486.0,
      "end_time": 98911.0,
      "text": "sometimes even praying right alongside me."
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 99943.0,
      "end_time": 102661.0,
      "text": "It was easy, as children, to come together,"
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 102685.0,
      "end_time": 104137.0,
      "text": "blend all of our beliefs"
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 104161.0,
      "end_time": 107616.0,
      "text": "to form our own unique, multicultural environment."
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 109258.0,
      "end_time": 110976.0,
      "text": "My name is Halima Aden"
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 111000.0,
      "end_time": 114680.0,
      "text": "and I&#39;m a black, Muslim, Somali-American from Kenya."
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 116300.0,
      "end_time": 118988.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 119120.0,
      "end_time": 121279.0,
      "text": "Some have called me a trailblazer --"
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 121303.0,
      "end_time": 124322.0,
      "text": "I was the first Muslim homecoming queen at my high school,"
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 124346.0,
      "end_time": 127109.0,
      "text": "the first Somali student senator at my college"
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 127133.0,
      "end_time": 129940.0,
      "text": "and the first hijab-wearing woman in many places,"
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 129964.0,
      "end_time": 132935.0,
      "text": "like the Miss Minnesota USA beauty pageant,"
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 132959.0,
      "end_time": 136180.0,
      "text": "the runways of Milan and New York Fashion Weeks"
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 136420.0,
      "end_time": 139800.0,
      "text": "and even on the historic cover of British \"Vogue.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 139778.0,
      "end_time": 140928.0,
      "text": "As you can see,"
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 141730.0,
      "end_time": 144849.0,
      "text": "I&#39;m not afraid to be the first, to step out on my own,"
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 144873.0,
      "end_time": 146469.0,
      "text": "to take risks and seek change,"
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 146493.0,
      "end_time": 148994.0,
      "text": "because that&#39;s what being a minority is about."
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 149180.0,
      "end_time": 151939.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s about using yourself as a vessel to create change"
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 151963.0,
      "end_time": 156476.0,
      "text": "and being a human representation for the power of diversity."
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 156500.0,
      "end_time": 160532.0,
      "text": "And now I use my platform to spread an important message of acceptance."
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 162472.0,
      "end_time": 164920.0,
      "text": "But it hasn&#39;t always been easy."
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 164726.0,
      "end_time": 168535.0,
      "text": "When we first arrived to the United States and made St. Louis, Missouri home,"
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 169464.0,
      "end_time": 173427.0,
      "text": "I remember asking my mom, \"Is this really America?\""
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 174194.0,
      "end_time": 177670.0,
      "text": "There were things that were sadly familiar,"
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 177920.0,
      "end_time": 178614.0,
      "text": "like hearing gunshots at night"
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 178638.0,
      "end_time": 180466.0,
      "text": "and the streets looking impoverished."
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 181328.0,
      "end_time": 184164.0,
      "text": "But there were things that were also very different."
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 184188.0,
      "end_time": 185875.0,
      "text": "Like when I started first grade,"
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 185900.0,
      "end_time": 188800.0,
      "text": "I noticed how the kids played in groups."
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 188320.0,
      "end_time": 190158.0,
      "text": "In America, we call them \"cliques.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 190182.0,
      "end_time": 192417.0,
      "text": "Back here, we all played together."
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 193240.0,
      "end_time": 194595.0,
      "text": "Gender didn&#39;t matter,"
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 194619.0,
      "end_time": 196764.0,
      "text": "and race most certainly never mattered."
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 197246.0,
      "end_time": 199405.0,
      "text": "I remember asking myself,"
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 199429.0,
      "end_time": 201341.0,
      "text": "\"Why don&#39;t they understand Swahili?"
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 201653.0,
      "end_time": 204591.0,
      "text": "Swahili is the language that brings people together.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 206605.0,
      "end_time": 207786.0,
      "text": "To make matters worse,"
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 207811.0,
      "end_time": 211513.0,
      "text": "the school I was enrolled in didn&#39;t have an English immersion program."
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 212330.0,
      "end_time": 214225.0,
      "text": "So everyday I would get up,"
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 214249.0,
      "end_time": 216344.0,
      "text": "go to school, sit in my desk"
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 216368.0,
      "end_time": 217585.0,
      "text": "and never learn a thing."
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 218773.0,
      "end_time": 220770.0,
      "text": "This is when I started losing hope,"
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 220794.0,
      "end_time": 223876.0,
      "text": "and I wanted nothing more than return to Kakuma,"
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 223900.0,
      "end_time": 225560.0,
      "text": "a refugee camp."
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 227838.0,
      "end_time": 230747.0,
      "text": "Soon, my mother learned that many Somalis found refuge"
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 230771.0,
      "end_time": 232713.0,
      "text": "in a small town in Minnesota."
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 233113.0,
      "end_time": 235883.0,
      "text": "So when I was eight, we moved to Minnesota."
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 237326.0,
      "end_time": 241440.0,
      "text": "My life changed as I met other students who spoke Somali,"
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 241464.0,
      "end_time": 244719.0,
      "text": "attended a school that had an English immersion program"
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 244743.0,
      "end_time": 247482.0,
      "text": "and found teachers that would go above and beyond,"
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 247506.0,
      "end_time": 250156.0,
      "text": "staying there after school hours and lunch breaks,"
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 250180.0,
      "end_time": 253306.0,
      "text": "dedicated to helping me find success in the classroom."
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 254427.0,
      "end_time": 259332.0,
      "text": "Being a child refugee has taught me that one could be stripped of everything:"
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 259356.0,
      "end_time": 262300.0,
      "text": "food, shelter, clean drinking water,"
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 262324.0,
      "end_time": 263913.0,
      "text": "even friendship,"
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 263937.0,
      "end_time": 267160.0,
      "text": "but the one thing that no one could ever take away from you"
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 267400.0,
      "end_time": 268371.0,
      "text": "is your education."
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 268778.0,
      "end_time": 271533.0,
      "text": "So I made studying my top priority"
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 271557.0,
      "end_time": 274105.0,
      "text": "and soon started flourishing within the classroom."
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 276154.0,
      "end_time": 279381.0,
      "text": "As I grew older, I became more aware of others"
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 279405.0,
      "end_time": 281811.0,
      "text": "and how they viewed my race and background."
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 282303.0,
      "end_time": 285670.0,
      "text": "Specifically, when I started wearing the head scarf known as a hijab."
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 286665.0,
      "end_time": 289318.0,
      "text": "When I first started wearing it, I was excited."
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 289342.0,
      "end_time": 294310.0,
      "text": "I remember admiring my mother&#39;s, and I wanted to emulate her beauty."
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 294550.0,
      "end_time": 296292.0,
      "text": "But when I started middle school,"
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 296316.0,
      "end_time": 299920.0,
      "text": "the students teased me about not having hair,"
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 299116.0,
      "end_time": 300726.0,
      "text": "so to prove them wrong,"
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 300750.0,
      "end_time": 303193.0,
      "text": "I started showing them my hair --"
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 303217.0,
      "end_time": 307320.0,
      "text": "something that goes against my beliefs, but something I felt pressured to do."
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 307943.0,
      "end_time": 310306.0,
      "text": "I wanted so badly to fit in at the time."
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 312620.0,
      "end_time": 317659.0,
      "text": "When I reflect on the issues of race, religion, identity,"
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 317683.0,
      "end_time": 319989.0,
      "text": "a lot of painful memories come to mind."
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 320644.0,
      "end_time": 323934.0,
      "text": "It would be easy for me to blame those of another culture"
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 323958.0,
      "end_time": 326684.0,
      "text": "for making me feel the pain I felt,"
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 326708.0,
      "end_time": 328121.0,
      "text": "but when I think deeper,"
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 328145.0,
      "end_time": 331490.0,
      "text": "I also recognize that the most impactful,"
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 331730.0,
      "end_time": 334580.0,
      "text": "positive, life-changing events that have happened to me"
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 334605.0,
      "end_time": 337224.0,
      "text": "are thanks to those people who are different than me."
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 338600.0,
      "end_time": 342259.0,
      "text": "It was at this moment that I decided to step outside of my comfort zone"
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 342283.0,
      "end_time": 345437.0,
      "text": "and compete in a pageant wearing a hijab and burkini."
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 346422.0,
      "end_time": 349519.0,
      "text": "I saw it as an opportunity to be a voice for women"
    },
    {
      "index": 112,
      "start_time": 349543.0,
      "end_time": 352750.0,
      "text": "who, like myself, had felt underrepresented."
    },
    {
      "index": 113,
      "start_time": 353767.0,
      "end_time": 355824.0,
      "text": "And although I didn&#39;t capture the crown,"
    },
    {
      "index": 114,
      "start_time": 355848.0,
      "end_time": 358299.0,
      "text": "that experience opened so many doors for me."
    },
    {
      "index": 115,
      "start_time": 358952.0,
      "end_time": 362943.0,
      "text": "I was receiving emails and messages from women all over the world,"
    },
    {
      "index": 116,
      "start_time": 362967.0,
      "end_time": 367157.0,
      "text": "telling me that I&#39;ve inspired them by simply staying true to myself."
    },
    {
      "index": 117,
      "start_time": 368107.0,
      "end_time": 370530.0,
      "text": "The other \"firsts\" kept coming."
    },
    {
      "index": 118,
      "start_time": 370763.0,
      "end_time": 375503.0,
      "text": "I was invited to New York City by fashion icon Carine Roitfeld"
    },
    {
      "index": 119,
      "start_time": 375528.0,
      "end_time": 377751.0,
      "text": "to shoot my very first editorial."
    },
    {
      "index": 120,
      "start_time": 378212.0,
      "end_time": 381776.0,
      "text": "It was around this time that I became the first hijab-wearing model,"
    },
    {
      "index": 121,
      "start_time": 381800.0,
      "end_time": 383344.0,
      "text": "and in my first year,"
    },
    {
      "index": 122,
      "start_time": 383368.0,
      "end_time": 386646.0,
      "text": "I graced the covers of nine fashion magazines."
    },
    {
      "index": 123,
      "start_time": 387210.0,
      "end_time": 389967.0,
      "text": "It was a whirlwind, to say the least."
    },
    {
      "index": 124,
      "start_time": 389991.0,
      "end_time": 392360.0,
      "text": "But with all the overnight success,"
    },
    {
      "index": 125,
      "start_time": 392384.0,
      "end_time": 395304.0,
      "text": "there was one thing that remained constant --"
    },
    {
      "index": 126,
      "start_time": 395328.0,
      "end_time": 399114.0,
      "text": "the thought that this could be what brings me back here to Kakuma,"
    },
    {
      "index": 127,
      "start_time": 399139.0,
      "end_time": 400773.0,
      "text": "the place that I call home."
    },
    {
      "index": 128,
      "start_time": 402780.0,
      "end_time": 406977.0,
      "text": "And just a few months ago, something incredible happened to me."
    },
    {
      "index": 129,
      "start_time": 407767.0,
      "end_time": 410409.0,
      "text": "I was in New York City, on a photo shoot,"
    },
    {
      "index": 130,
      "start_time": 410434.0,
      "end_time": 413483.0,
      "text": "when I met South Sudanese model Adut Akech,"
    },
    {
      "index": 131,
      "start_time": 413507.0,
      "end_time": 416628.0,
      "text": "who also happened to be born right here in Kakuma."
    },
    {
      "index": 132,
      "start_time": 418163.0,
      "end_time": 421890.0,
      "text": "That experience in itself is the definition of hope."
    },
    {
      "index": 133,
      "start_time": 422399.0,
      "end_time": 424339.0,
      "text": "I mean, just imagine:"
    },
    {
      "index": 134,
      "start_time": 424363.0,
      "end_time": 428500.0,
      "text": "two girls born in the same refugee camp,"
    },
    {
      "index": 135,
      "start_time": 428290.0,
      "end_time": 431971.0,
      "text": "reunited for the first time on the cover of British \"Vogue.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 136,
      "start_time": 432557.0,
      "end_time": 438890.0,
      "text": "(Applause and cheering)"
    },
    {
      "index": 137,
      "start_time": 438740.0,
      "end_time": 442503.0,
      "text": "I was given the distinct pleasure of partnering up with UNICEF,"
    },
    {
      "index": 138,
      "start_time": 442527.0,
      "end_time": 446150.0,
      "text": "knowing firsthand the work that they do for children in need."
    },
    {
      "index": 139,
      "start_time": 447286.0,
      "end_time": 448946.0,
      "text": "And I want you to remember"
    },
    {
      "index": 140,
      "start_time": 448970.0,
      "end_time": 451976.0,
      "text": "that although the children here may be refugees,"
    },
    {
      "index": 141,
      "start_time": 453160.0,
      "end_time": 454913.0,
      "text": "they are children."
    },
    {
      "index": 142,
      "start_time": 455230.0,
      "end_time": 460325.0,
      "text": "They deserve every opportunity to flourish, to hope, to dream --"
    },
    {
      "index": 143,
      "start_time": 461114.0,
      "end_time": 462741.0,
      "text": "to be successful."
    },
    {
      "index": 144,
      "start_time": 464522.0,
      "end_time": 469233.0,
      "text": "My story began right here in Kakuma refugee camp,"
    },
    {
      "index": 145,
      "start_time": 469257.0,
      "end_time": 471110.0,
      "text": "a place of hope."
    },
    {
      "index": 146,
      "start_time": 471501.0,
      "end_time": 472652.0,
      "text": "Thank you."
    },
    {
      "index": 147,
      "start_time": 472676.0,
      "end_time": 477260.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    }
  ]
}